				\begin{document}$${\text{R}}_{\text{adj}}^{2}(\text{\%})=100-\left(\frac{\text{N}-1}{\text{N}-\text{M}}\right)\left(100-{\text{R}}^{2}\right)$$\end{document}where M is the number of parameters in the models and R2 is the coefficient of determination between the experimental data and their values predicted by the mathematical models.
